(NSString *) + getVersionString
 Returns the public version. Returns the official version of the PCL library in the form of “@(#)PROGRAM:iSMP PROJECT:iSMP-x.y”. This is the function to use to check the version of the PCL library. To just get the version number, get the substring of the returned NSString object starting from index 30. More...
 

Detailed Description

Methods to retrieve information about the library version, must not be used (will be deprecated in the future).

+ (NSString *) getVersionString

Returns the public version. Returns the official version of the PCL library in the form of “@(#)PROGRAM:iSMP PROJECT:iSMP-x.y”. This is the function to use to check the version of the PCL library. To just get the version number, get the substring of the returned NSString object starting from index 30.

Returns
The version string
